) annually 2.000 billion U.S. dollars. To form a common market, a manufacturing facility and general distribution, the AEC will conduct free flow of basic factors: capital, goods, services, investment and skilled labor. To cope with this competition requires businesses to constantly improve their competitiveness through clearly defined goods and services which they have a competitive advantage over, improving business capacity, and quality of products and services, actively promoting and branding,... Specifically, Vietnam enterprises should focus on improving: innovation in business management - financial management innovation to use capital effective; Innovation and technology equipment; market development, business networking, relationship with the consumer; applying international standards in product management; and improve the management and human resources training. This is inconsistent with the context of the fierce competition; the slower or non-reliable information will result in the SMEs managers to make incorrect decisions and mistakes. So, how to meet the information timely and accurate decision-making executives? As long as there is an effective accounting information system (AIS) by computer, it would not only solve the problem of handling and provide information quickly, promptly and accurately but also increase labor productivity of the accounting. This is the basis to streamline the structure, improve efficiency of operations and as basis for making decisions to achieve the objectives of the proposed business. Therefore, determining the economic efficiency of the system is a very important problem for the SMEs.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'he-thong-thong-tin-ke-toan-anh-huong-den-hieu-qua-cua-cac-doanh-nghiep-vua-va-nho-viet-nam-khi-cong-dong-kinh-te-asean-hinh-thanh', '', '', '2015-11-05 15:26:22', '2015-11-05 08:26:22', '', 0, 'http://epaper.edu.vn/?post_type=product&#038;p=3737', 0, 'product', '', 0),
